[Tue 2026-04-21 11:54 CDT] Upgrade the Kalshi weather trading system — Priority 5: Brier score calibration tracking.

## Repo
~/.openclaw/workspace/kalshi-weather/

## What is Brier score?
Brier score measures forecast calibration: BS = (pWin - outcome)²
- 0.0 = perfect, 0.25 = coin flip, higher = worse
- Lower is better
- If we say 70% confidence and win 70% of those trades → well calibrated
- This tells us if our ensemble pWin is actually predictive

## What to build

### Step 1 — Add Brier score calculation to `src/paper.ts`

Add a new exported function `computeBrierStats()`:

```ts
export interface BrierStats {
  brierScore: number;          // mean Brier score across all calibrated trades
  totalCalibrated: number;     // trades with ensemble_pwin recorded
  byConfidence: {
    high:   { brier: number; count: number; winRate: number } | null;
    medium: { brier: number; count: number; winRate: number } | null;
    low:    { brier: number; count: number; winRate: number } | null;
  };
  calibrationBuckets: Array<{  // for calibration curve
    pwinBucket: string;        // e.g. "0.5-0.6"
    predicted: number;         // midpoint of bucket
    actual: number;            // actual win rate in this bucket
    count: number;
  }>;
}

export function computeBrierStats(): BrierStats | null {
  const trades = readTrades();
  const settled = trades.filter(t => 
    t.status !== 'open' && 
    t.pnl !== undefined &&
    t.ensemble_pwin !== undefined
  );

  if (settled.length === 0) return null;

  // Overall Brier score
  const brierScores = settled.map(t => {
    const outcome = t.status === 'won' ? 1 : 0;
    const pWin = t.ensemble_pwin!;
    return Math.pow(pWin - outcome, 2);
  });
  const brierScore = brierScores.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / brierScores.length;

  // By confidence level
  const byConf = (['high', 'medium', 'low'] as const).map(level => {
    const group = settled.filter(t => t.model_confidence === level);
    if (group.length === 0) return [level, null] as const;
    const bs = group.reduce((s, t) => s + Math.pow(t.ensemble_pwin! - (t.status === 'won' ? 1 : 0), 2), 0) / group.length;
    const winRate = group.filter(t => t.status === 'won').length / group.length;
    return [level, { brier: Math.round(bs * 1000) / 1000, count: group.length, winRate: Math.round(winRate * 1000) / 1000 }] as const;
  });

  // Calibration buckets: 0.5-0.6, 0.6-0.7, 0.7-0.8, 0.8-0.9, 0.9-1.0
  const buckets = [[0.5, 0.6], [0.6, 0.7], [0.7, 0.8], [0.8, 0.9], [0.9, 1.0]];
  const calibrationBuckets = buckets.map(([lo, hi]) => {
    const group = settled.filter(t => t.ensemble_pwin! >= lo && t.ensemble_pwin! < hi);
    const actual = group.length > 0 ? group.filter(t => t.status === 'won').length / group.length : 0;
    return {
      pwinBucket: `${lo}-${hi}`,
      predicted: (lo + hi) / 2,
      actual: Math.round(actual * 1000) / 1000,
      count: group.length,
    };
  }).filter(b => b.count > 0);

  return {
    brierScore: Math.round(brierScore * 1000) / 1000,
    totalCalibrated: settled.length,
    byConfidence: { high: byConf[0][1] ?? null, medium: byConf[1][1] ?? null, low: byConf[2][1] ?? null },
    calibrationBuckets,
  };
}
```

### Step 2 — Add Brier stats to the API server

In `src/api-server.ts`, add a new endpoint:

```ts
app.get('/api/brier', (_req, res) => {
  const stats = computeBrierStats();
  res.json(stats || { error: 'No calibrated trades yet' });
});
```

Import `computeBrierStats` from `./paper`.

### Step 3 — Add Brier score panel to the dashboard

In `dashboard/src/components/PaperTrades.tsx`:

1. Add a `BrierStats` interface matching the API response shape.

2. Fetch brier stats:
```ts
const [brierStats, setBrierStats] = useState<BrierStats | null>(null)

useEffect(() => {
  fetch(`${api}/api/brier`)
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(d => d.brierScore !== undefined ? setBrierStats(d) : null)
    .catch(() => {})
}, [api])
```

3. Add a "Model Calibration" section below the City Performance / Model Accuracy panels:

```tsx
{brierStats && (
  <div className="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 p-5">
    <h3 className="text-sm font-medium text-white mb-3">Model Calibration (Brier Score)</h3>
    <p className="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-4">
      Brier score measures forecast accuracy: 0.0 = perfect, 0.25 = coin flip. 
      Lower is better. Based on {brierStats.totalCalibrated} trades with ensemble data.
    </p>
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4">
      <MiniCard label="Overall Brier" value={brierStats.brierScore.toFixed(3)} 
        positive={brierStats.brierScore < 0.2} />
      {brierStats.byConfidence.high && (
        <MiniCard label="High Conf Brier" value={brierStats.byConfidence.high.brier.toFixed(3)}
          positive={brierStats.byConfidence.high.brier < 0.2} />
      )}
      {brierStats.byConfidence.medium && (
        <MiniCard label="Med Conf Brier" value={brierStats.byConfidence.medium.brier.toFixed(3)}
          positive={brierStats.byConfidence.medium.brier < 0.2} />
      )}
    </div>
    {brierStats.calibrationBuckets.length > 0 && (
      <div>
        <p className="text-xs text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Calibration Curve</p>
        <table className="w-full text-xs">
          <thead>
            <tr className="text-slate-500">
              <th className="text-left py-1">pWin Range</th>
              <th className="text-center py-1">Predicted</th>
              <th className="text-center py-1">Actual Win%</th>
              <th className="text-center py-1">Trades</th>
              <th className="text-center py-1">Calibration</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {brierStats.calibrationBuckets.map(b => {
              const diff = Math.abs(b.actual - b.predicted)
              const calibColor = diff < 0.05 ? 'text-emerald-400' : diff < 0.15 ? 'text-yellow-400' : 'text-red-400'
              return (
                <tr key={b.pwinBucket} className="border-t border-slate-700/50">
                  <td className="py-2 font-mono">{b.pwinBucket}</td>
                  <td className="py-2 text-center">{(b.predicted * 100).toFixed(0)}%</td>
                  <td className={`py-2 text-center font-mono ${calibColor}`}>{(b.actual * 100).toFixed(1)}%</td>
                  <td className="py-2 text-center text-slate-400">{b.count}</td>
                  <td className={`py-2 text-center ${calibColor}`}>
                    {diff < 0.05 ? '✓ Good' : diff < 0.15 ? '~ OK' : '✗ Off'}
                  </td>
                </tr>
              )
            })}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    )}
  </div>
)}
```

### Step 4 — Add Brier score to daily Telegram summary

In `src/paper.ts`, update `printPaperSummary()` to include Brier stats at the bottom:

```ts
const brier = computeBrierStats();
if (brier) {
  console.log(`\nModel Calibration (Brier Score):`);
  console.log(`Overall Brier:   ${brier.brierScore} (${brier.totalCalibrated} calibrated trades)`);
  if (brier.byConfidence.high) console.log(`High conf Brier: ${brier.byConfidence.high.brier} (${brier.byConfidence.high.count} trades, ${(brier.byConfidence.high.winRate*100).toFixed(1)}% win rate)`);
}
```

## After changes
1. Run `cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/kalshi-weather/dashboard && npm run build` — 0 errors required
2. Confirm `/api/brier` returns valid JSON (may say "no calibrated trades yet" since existing trades predate ensemble_pwin — that's fine)
3. Report what you built

## Note on existing data
Most of our 57 settled trades were logged before P1 added `ensemble_pwin`. So Brier stats will start empty and populate as new trades come in with real ensemble data. That's expected — don't try to backfill.

